dcterms:description: A binary classification dataset that predicts the onset of diabetes within 5 years based on features from patient medical records. It contains 768 observations and 8 input features (Glucose, Blood Pressure, Insulin, BMI, Age, etc.) with a binary output indicating eventual disease onset.
dcterms:title: UCI Pima Indians Diabetes dataset

dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset created for experiments, consisting of 100 features and 200,000 instances. The dataset is designed to allow control over each attribute and simulate various scenarios, including low and high density regions and correlations between features.
dcterms:title: Synthetic dataset
